{{Quote|Welcome to the Expeditionary Library. You are among the very few non-Chiss to step through these doors.|Tris, to the team looking for Zonama Sekot|<ref name="Refugee" />}}
The '''Expeditionary Library''', also known as the '''Chiss data library''', was a massive underground [[Library/Legends|library]] located under the [[Water/Legends|ice]] of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy's]] [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Csilla/Legends|Csilla]]. The library contained the documents and works produced from the [[Chiss Expansionary Defense Force]]'s exploration of the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]], with most of it translated into [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]] and in [[Book/Legends|written form]] to prevent losing any data to ice storms. In [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]], a [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]]&ndash;[[Imperial Remnant]] group led by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] visited the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] library in hopes of finding the location of the [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] world [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]], and succeeded in pinpointing the position of the planet to the [[Klasse Ephemora system/Legends|Klasse Ephemora system]].

==Description==
{{Quote|The Chiss have always stored sensitive information in this fashion. It is safe, secure, and permanent. We have lost too much data in ice storms to trust other, more complicated forms of storage.''"<br />"''But how are we going to find anything? We can't do keyword searches through&hellip;''this''!|[[Tris (Chiss)|Tris]] and [[Danni Quee]], regarding books|<ref name="Refugee" />}}
[[File:ChissTEA.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The Expeditionary Library was located on the icy planet of Csilla (pictured).]]
The Expeditionary Library,<ref name="Refugee" /> also known as the Chiss data library,<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> was located in a remote sector on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Csilla/Legends|Csilla]], the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]] in the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]], and was some distance away from the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[City/Legends|city]] [[Ac'siel]]. Situated deep underneath the [[Water/Legends|ice]] that covered Csilla, the [[Library/Legends|library]] was in a secure installation and featured a pair of large, sturdy doors that permitted access to the facility. Taking up the size of a [[Hangar/Legends|docking bay]], the Expeditionary Library was rectangular in shape and had four levels of walkways&mdash;accessed by steep stairwells&mdash;that adorned the walls. [[Color/Legends|Yellow]] lights hung from the ceiling of the library, supported by cables, and the main floor was partitioned by a multitude of shelves arranged in rows, with narrow aisles between them. A large square table made of [[Snow-wood|snowwood]] was located in the center of the Expeditionary Library, and it had room enough to seat at least twenty people. The [[Atmosphere/Legends|air]] in the library was still, warm, and dry.<ref name="Refugee" />

The Expeditionary Library housed the mission reports, contact histories, [[Sentientologist|anthropological]] essays, and [[Xenobiologist/Legends|xenobiology]] tracts from the [[Chiss Expansionary Defense Force]]'s exploration of the Unknown Regions of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], all stored in [[Book/Legends|book]] form, as data stored by technological means could be destroyed by ice storms; thus, the library did not have any [[Viewscreen/Legends|holoscreens]]. Because all of the sources in the library were in written form, certain methods helped when searching for a subject, and the contents of the library were scrupulously cataloged. The majority of the text available in the library was translated into [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]], though some of it remained in [[Cheunh/Legends|Cheunh]], the [[Language/Legends|language]] of the Chiss [[Species/Legends|species]].<ref name="Refugee" />

==History==
{{Quote|I propose that the Skywalkers and their allies be given full access to the Expeditionary Library here on Csilla, in order that they might conduct their search in safety.|[[Chief Navigator]] [[Peita Aabe]]|<ref name="Refugee" />}}
The Expeditionary Library was in existence<ref name="Refugee" /> by the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[27,000 BBY/Legends|27,000 BBY]].<ref name="Creation date note" /> During their childhoods, every Chiss absorbed the basic facts provided by the volumes among the stacks of the library after years of intense schooling. It possessed the most extensive collection of information on the [[Mnggal-Mnggal]] entity&mdash;including the [[Galactic coordinates/Legends|coordinates]] of its [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]], [[Mugg Fallow]], and all possible information on its origins. Some individuals considered the [[Lugubraa]] elder [[Lorgrombo]] to be the low-tech fringe equivalent of the great Expeditionary Library.<ref name="TUR">''[[The Unknown Regions]]''</ref>

By the year [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]]<ref name="ERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], when the [[Yuuzhan Vong galaxy|extra-galactic]] [[Yuuzhan Vong]] invaded the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]], the Chiss Expansionary Defense Force's exploration of the Unknown Regions had been going on for [[Standard century/Legends|centuries]]. As a result, the library contained millions, possibly billions, of pages of content. That year, a [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]]&ndash;[[Imperial Remnant]] team led by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] visited Csilla in its [[Hunt for Zonama Sekot|search]] for the [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]]-traveling, [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] planet [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]].<ref name="Refugee" />

The representatives of the [[Ruling Families/Legends|Ruling Families]] of the Chiss and the Chiss Expansionary Defense Force granted the team access to the Expeditionary Library for two [[Standard day/Legends|days]] and provided a guide, [[Tris (Chiss)|Tris]]. The members of the team became part of the few non-Chiss to have ever entered the Expeditionary Library. In searching for Zonama Sekot, they followed a trail of references to the wandering planet in the reports from the Chiss Expansionary Defense Force and endured a [[Attack on Soontir Fel|skirmish]] with Chiss elements who disapproved of the changes being made due to outsider influence. With the help of young Csilla resident [[Wynssa Fel]], the team sought to find the current position of the living planet by searching for [[Star system/Legends|systems]] that had gained planets in the previous sixty years using an algorithm Fel created on a [[Holopad/Legends|holopad]]. When that failed, a change to searching for [[Moon/Legends|moon]] acquisitions gave the team the location of Zonama Sekot: the [[Klasse Ephemora system/Legends|Klasse Ephemora system]].<ref name="Refugee" /> The role of the Expeditionary Library in the Yuuzhan Vong War was recorded in a [[The New Essential Chronology (in-universe)|historical document]] published in [[36 ABY]] by the [[Historical Council]] of the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]].<ref name="TNEC" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Expeditionary Library appeared in [[Sean Williams]] and [[Shane Dix]]'s [[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee|''Force Heretic II: Refugee'']], a [[2003]] novel released as part of [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''The New Jedi Order'']] series.<ref name="Refugee" />

